<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.63119/15</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Vienna</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frazier</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-06"><hi rend="italic">September 6,
                                    1921</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received September 20.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 309</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my despatch No. 306 of
                            to-day’s date, I have the honor to transmit herewith enclosed a
                            corrected copy of the treaty of peace between the United States and
                            Austria dated August 24, 1921, signed by the Austrian Federal Chancellor
                            and myself.<note n="8" xml:id="d228fn8">See final text, <ref target="#pg_274">p. 274</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur Hugh
                            Frazier</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>